  <summary date="2020-04-14T18:58:27Z" status="Introduced in House">Pandemic Healthcare Access Act

This bill preserves the eligibility of health savings account (HSA) participants covered by any health plan&#160;during the coronavirus emergency period. The coronavirus emergency period is the period beginning on March 13, 2020, and ending on the later of (1) the last day on which a presidential declaration of emergency under the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act with respect to the coronavirus (i.e., the virus that causes COVID-19)&#160;is in effect, or (2) the last day on which&#160;a presidential declaration of national emergency under the National Emergencies Act with respect to the coronavirus&#160;is in effect.</summary>
